    </div>

    <!-- ADULT VS KIDS -->
    <h2 id="adult-vs-kids">How Adult Elderberry Differs From Kids' Formulas</h2>

    <p>If you are buying elderberry for yourself, do not buy a children's formulation. The differences are not just dose — adult and kids' elderberry products are formulated differently across four dimensions:</p>

    <div class="vs-strip">
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Extract Concentration</strong>
        <p><strong>Adult:</strong> 100-200mg standardized sambucus extract per serving (some premium products up to 350mg). <strong>Kids:</strong> 50-100mg, calibrated for lower body weight. Adults using kids' formulas typically need to double the serving, which often becomes more expensive than buying the adult version directly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Immune Cofactors</strong>
        <p><strong>Adult:</strong> Often includes zinc 7.5-15mg, vitamin C 60-90mg, sometimes echinacea or propolis. <strong>Kids:</strong> Lower zinc (2.5-5mg), excludes echinacea under age 12 in many formulas, no propolis. Adult cofactor doses are calibrated to clinical research; kids' doses are deliberately conservative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Gummy Format and Flavor</strong>
        <p><strong>Adult:</strong> Larger gummies, more complex botanical flavors (often slightly tart from the elderberry itself). <strong>Kids:</strong> Smaller gummies sized to prevent choking, sweeter and milder flavor profiles, sometimes shaped as bears or fruit shapes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Sugar Content</strong>
        <p><strong>Adult:</strong> Often 1-3g per serving, with more sugar-free options available. <strong>Kids:</strong> Frequently 2-4g per serving (palatability matters more for adherence in children). Adults watching sugar intake should specifically seek adult formulations sweetened with stevia, monk fruit, or allulose.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>If you have both adults and children in the household needing elderberry support, buy the appropriate formula for each group — see our <a href="/immunity/elderberry-gummies-for-kids/">elderberry gummies for kids</a> ranking alongside this adult guide. Sharing a single formulation across the household typically results in either underdosing the adults or overdosing the children.</p>

